"# Full-Stack System Design Projects\n\nProduction-grade full-stack projects demonstrating enterprise-level system design with Java Spring Boot, RabbitMQ, and modern frontend frameworks.\n\n## Projects\n\n### 1. [Real-Time Multi-Tenant Job Scheduling Platform](./job-scheduling-platform)\nA distributed job scheduling and execution platform with priority queues, dead letter exchanges, and real-time execution monitoring.\n\n**Backend:** Java 17, Spring Boot 3.2, RabbitMQ, PostgreSQL, Redis, WebSocket\n**Frontend:** Angular 17\n\n**Key System Design Concepts:**\n- Competing consumers with RabbitMQ priority queues (1-10 levels)\n- Dead Letter Exchange with TTL-based delayed retry\n- Distributed locking (Redis SETNX) for cron trigger deduplication\n- Fan-out exchange for real-time event broadcasting\n- Multi-tenant isolation via routing keys\n- Worker heartbeat protocol\n- Execution state machine (PENDING -> QUEUED -> RUNNING -> COMPLETED/FAILED)\n\n**Features:**\n- 4 job types: HTTP Call, Shell Script, SQL Query, Python Script\n- Cron-based scheduling with distributed lock coordination\n- Real-time log streaming via WebSocket (STOMP)\n- Angular dashboard with job builder, execution monitor, and terminal-style log viewer\n- Worker health monitoring with heartbeat tracking\n\n---\n\n### 2. [Async API Orchestration Gateway](./api-orchestration-gateway)\nA platform for visually composing and executing API workflows asynchronously through RabbitMQ, with saga compensation and circuit breaker patterns.\n\n**Backend:** Java 17, Spring Boot 3.2, RabbitMQ, PostgreSQL, Redis, WebSocket, WebClient\n**Frontend:** React 18 + TypeScript\n\n**Key System Design Concepts:**\n- Orchestration pattern with correlation IDs for async request-response\n- Topic exchange routing for step-type-based message dispatch\n- Saga pattern with compensating transactions (reverse-order rollback)\n- Circuit breaker pattern (closed/open/half-open) per endpoint via Redis\n- Fan-out/fan-in aggregation pattern\n- Back-pressure via RabbitMQ consumer prefetch limits\n- JSONPath-based data transformation between workflow steps\n\n**Features:**\n- 6 step types: HTTP Call, Transform, Condition (branching), Delay, Aggregate (fan-in), Script\n- Visual flow builder with React Flow (drag-and-drop canvas)\n- Real-time execution tracing via WebSocket\n- Circuit breaker dashboard with per-endpoint health monitoring\n- Configurable retry strategies (fixed, exponential backoff)\n- Flow validation with cycle detection\n\n---\n\n## Architecture & Design Patterns\n\n| Pattern | Job Scheduler | API Gateway |\n|---------|:---:|:---:|\n| Priority Queues | Yes | - |\n| Dead Letter Exchange | Yes | Yes |\n| Delayed Retry (TTL + DLX) | Yes | Yes |\n| Competing Consumers | Yes | Yes |\n| Fan-out Exchange | Yes | Yes |\n| Topic Exchange Routing | - | Yes |\n| Correlation IDs | - | Yes |\n| Saga / Compensation | - | Yes |\n| Circuit Breaker | - | Yes |\n| Distributed Locking | Yes | - |\n| Multi-tenancy | Yes | - |\n| Worker Heartbeat | Yes | - |\n| Execution State Machine | Yes | Yes |\n| WebSocket (STOMP) | Yes | Yes |\n\n## Quick Start\n\nEach project includes Docker Compose:\n\n```bash\n# Job Scheduling Platform\ncd job-scheduling-platform && docker compose up --build\n# Backend: http://localhost:8081/swagger-ui.html\n# RabbitMQ: http://localhost:15672 (guest/guest)\n\n# API Orchestration Gateway\ncd api-orchestration-gateway && docker compose up --build\n# Backend: http://localhost:8082/swagger-ui.html\n# RabbitMQ: http://localhost:15672 (guest/guest)\n```\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|-----------|\n| Backend | Java 17, Spring Boot 3.2 |\n| Messaging | RabbitMQ (AMQP) |\n| Database | PostgreSQL |\n| Cache/Locks | Redis |\n| Real-time | WebSocket (STOMP) |\n| Frontend 1 | Angular 17 (TypeScript, SCSS) |\n| Frontend 2 | React 18 (TypeScript, Vite, React Flow) |\n| Containerization | Docker, Docker Compose |\n\n## Author\n**Vakkalakula Lokesh** | lokeshvakkalakula619@gmail.com\n"